1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,400
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,400 --> 00:00:02,667
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:06,667 --> 00:00:07,667
My goodness!

4
00:00:07,867 --> 00:00:08,867
Bit Na!

5
00:00:09,367 --> 00:00:10,400
(Episode 51)

6
00:00:14,067 --> 00:00:15,667
Min Ho's mom...

7
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:17,167
I mean, Madam.

8
00:00:17,867 --> 00:00:18,867
Kang Yeon Ja.

9
00:00:19,467 --> 00:00:20,900
What brings you to my house?

10
00:00:21,067 --> 00:00:22,067
Sorry?

11
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,100
It's nothing.

12
00:00:24,567 --> 00:00:26,000
Wait, Madam!

13
00:00:28,300 --> 00:00:29,300
What's her problem?

14
00:00:32,667 --> 00:00:33,667
Bit Na.

15
00:00:34,767 --> 00:00:36,300
This necklace!

16
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:38,367
What is it, Grandma?

17
00:00:38,567 --> 00:00:39,567
Give it to me. Hurry!

18
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:41,767
Where did you find this...

19
00:00:41,767 --> 00:00:42,967
Grandma.

20
00:00:44,467 --> 00:00:45,467
I mean...

21
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:47,267
Okay, all right.

22
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:48,800
It's okay. I'm sorry.

23
00:00:49,100 --> 00:00:50,067
It's okay. Don't cry.

24
00:00:50,367 --> 00:00:51,367
Bit Na, I'm sorry.

25
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:52,667
It's okay.

26
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:55,967
My goodness.

27
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:57,667
How is this even possible?

28
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,400
Unbelievable!

29
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:00,400
My goodness!

30
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:02,667
Well, look who it is.

31
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:05,167
Aren't you the Center Spot?

32
00:01:05,367 --> 00:01:07,000
Yes, hello.

33
00:01:07,467 --> 00:01:10,567
What brings you all the way...

34
00:01:10,567 --> 00:01:12,267
to this humble neighborhood?

35
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:15,400
Did you come to see how your son's doing?

36
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:16,500
No way.

37
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:17,900
Hey...

38
00:01:18,667 --> 00:01:19,667
That rude woman!

39
00:01:34,667 --> 00:01:36,967
I washed my face, Grandma.

40
00:01:37,867 --> 00:01:38,900
Are you done crying?

41
00:01:40,167 --> 00:01:42,000
I'm really sorry for yelling earlier.

42
00:01:42,867 --> 00:01:43,967
It's fine.

43
00:01:44,667 --> 00:01:47,267
I shouldn't have touched your things
without permission.

44
00:01:47,467 --> 00:01:49,367
It was my fault.

45
00:01:49,667 --> 00:01:51,300
No.

46
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,167
You were just bored and playing around.

47
00:01:55,167 --> 00:01:57,500
But that lady who came earlier...

48
00:01:57,500 --> 00:01:59,067
Did she say anything to you?

49
00:01:59,267 --> 00:02:02,067
She asked whose necklace it was.

50
00:02:02,467 --> 00:02:05,667
But she looked shocked when she saw it.

51
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,067
Shocked?

52
00:02:08,667 --> 00:02:12,067
Grandma,
I want to go visit Auntie Cho Rong.

53
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:13,100
Auntie Cho Rong?

54
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:14,400
Sure, go have fun.

55
00:02:14,567 --> 00:02:16,067
Don't stay too long.

56
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:17,667
- Yes, Grandma.
- Okay.

57
00:02:20,167 --> 00:02:22,367
Did she come here
knowing Team Manager Ko lives here?

58
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,400
No.

59
00:02:25,167 --> 00:02:26,567
If she knew, she would've said something.

60
00:02:28,867 --> 00:02:30,867
What?
Who did you say Mother's daughter is?

61
00:02:32,267 --> 00:02:34,467
Someone might hear. Keep your voice down.

62
00:02:35,667 --> 00:02:36,800
Are you sure?

63
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:39,867
You're not getting carried away
with one of your wild theories again?

64
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:41,100
No.

65
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:42,667
It's exactly the same
as Mother's necklace.

66
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:44,500
And inside it was...

67
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:47,267
that photo of Mother when she was young.

68
00:02:48,367 --> 00:02:49,867
Goodness, how is this even possible?

69
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:51,300
That woman...

70
00:02:51,300 --> 00:02:53,767
I wondered how she spoke French
so fluently.

71
00:02:54,567 --> 00:02:55,800
French...

72
00:02:56,667 --> 00:02:57,800
Adopted overseas in France.

73
00:02:59,067 --> 00:03:01,200
Everything fits perfectly.

74
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,267
My goodness.

75
00:03:02,867 --> 00:03:04,100
It was right under our eyes all along.

76
00:03:06,167 --> 00:03:07,800
It's "noses."

77
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:10,067
Under our noses.

78
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:12,367
Why would it be under our noses?

79
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:13,767
Talk some sense.

80
00:03:14,967 --> 00:03:15,967
My head hurts.

81
00:03:16,267 --> 00:03:17,267
Seriously...

82
00:03:17,567 --> 00:03:18,700
- What do we do?
- Mr. Cho.

83
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:24,700
Hello, Madam.

84
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:25,700
Yes.

85
00:03:25,767 --> 00:03:27,467
Mr. Cho, what's going on now?

86
00:03:28,567 --> 00:03:30,267
What's the matter?

87
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:32,967
Me? It's nothing.

88
00:03:34,467 --> 00:03:37,867
I've selected a few candidate sites
you mentioned before.

89
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:40,600
Really? Great work.

90
00:03:40,967 --> 00:03:42,667
All right, you can go now.

91
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,967
Yes, then.

92
00:03:49,867 --> 00:03:50,867
Because of him...

93
00:03:51,167 --> 00:03:53,267
Honey, fire Mr. Cho immediately.

94
00:03:53,867 --> 00:03:54,867
What?

95
00:03:55,367 --> 00:03:58,267
Driving you to and from work,
and coming to our house all the time...

96
00:03:58,467 --> 00:04:00,767
What if he finds out his wife
is Mother's daughter?

97
00:04:01,367 --> 00:04:02,867
That would be a disaster.

98
00:04:03,867 --> 00:04:04,867
But listen.

99
00:04:04,867 --> 00:04:06,867
Just because I'm the CEO...

100
00:04:07,367 --> 00:04:10,000
doesn't mean I can fire an employee
for no reason.

101
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:11,967
That's the law.

102
00:04:11,967 --> 00:04:13,767
Then what do we do?

103
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,367
Crystal, listen carefully...

104
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:19,100
to what I'm about to say.

105
00:04:19,767 --> 00:04:22,067
You see, your thoughts...

106
00:04:22,067 --> 00:04:23,800
Everything about you,
from your face to your back,

107
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:26,867
is completely transparent.

108
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:29,667
You could slip up in front of Mother.

109
00:04:29,667 --> 00:04:31,967
So from this moment on,

110
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:34,267
you need a poker face around her.

111
00:04:34,267 --> 00:04:35,267
Watch closely.

112
00:04:35,267 --> 00:04:36,300
You know what a poker face is, right?

113
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:41,167
- A poker face.
- Of course I do.

114
00:04:42,467 --> 00:04:43,467
A poker face.

115
00:04:44,467 --> 00:04:45,467
Wait!

116
00:04:45,667 --> 00:04:47,767
I finally figured it out.

117
00:04:48,667 --> 00:04:49,967
How to crack the safe code.

118
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,967
How?

119
00:04:53,367 --> 00:04:55,767
Ask Mr. Cho for his wife's birthday.

120
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:56,800
That's it.

121
00:04:57,067 --> 00:04:58,067
Crystal!

122
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,600
You're a genius.

123
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,667
That's perfect.

124
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,300
- A poker face.
- A poker face.

125
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:05,300
Now...

126
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:14,267
Knowing Seung Ri, it can't be too flashy.

127
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:18,000
It has to be a proposal
with a story behind it.

128
00:05:19,367 --> 00:05:21,267
A story...

129
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:23,367
Come in.

130
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:27,500
Hey.

131
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,467
It's the proposal for the Joy upgrade.

132
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:30,600
I see.

133
00:05:30,667 --> 00:05:31,667
What do you think?

134
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:34,700
I think Mr. Han Ji Hun
may have reached his limit.

135
00:05:34,867 --> 00:05:35,867
Take a look.

136
00:05:37,767 --> 00:05:39,367
Did you talk to your mother?

137
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:42,667
Yes. It won't happen again.

138
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:44,467
If anything like that happens again,

139
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:45,767
call me no matter what.

140
00:05:46,767 --> 00:05:50,067
I'm willing to take the heat.

141
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:52,267
Well, then...

142
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:02,800
I'm not sure if this is the right time.

143
00:06:31,567 --> 00:06:34,067
I've finished organizing
the existing Joy system.

144
00:06:34,567 --> 00:06:35,567
Already?

145
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:37,367
Didn't you say it would take three days?

146
00:06:38,267 --> 00:06:39,767
I worked on it nonstop for two days,

147
00:06:39,767 --> 00:06:41,267
so I finished earlier than expected.

148
00:06:41,867 --> 00:06:43,967
I just emailed it to you.

149
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,400
I also printed it out for convenience,
so please take a look.

150
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,600
If there are any revisions,
I'll make them right away.

151
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,200
Good work.

152
00:06:58,867 --> 00:07:00,067
Okay.

153
00:07:02,867 --> 00:07:04,100
Wasn't it urgent?

154
00:07:04,767 --> 00:07:07,600
You halted our team's work
and had her spend two full days on it.

155
00:07:07,867 --> 00:07:08,967
The least you could do is review it.

156
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,200
Excuse me?

157
00:07:12,067 --> 00:07:13,500
Okay.

158
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,267
I'll review it soon.

159
00:07:26,467 --> 00:07:28,567
Yes? All right.

160
00:07:30,367 --> 00:07:31,567
I'm heading to the CPO's office.

161
00:07:31,567 --> 00:07:33,100
Let's have a team meeting in 30 minutes.

162
00:07:33,467 --> 00:07:34,467
Yes, Team Manager.

163
00:07:43,267 --> 00:07:44,267
It's me.

164
00:07:45,067 --> 00:07:47,167
Can you make some time after work?

165
00:07:49,667 --> 00:07:53,200
I'm sorry about grabbing your collar
that day.

166
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:56,800
You know how I lose all reason
when it comes to Seung Ri.

167
00:07:58,367 --> 00:08:00,367
It's fine. Just get to the point.

168
00:08:00,767 --> 00:08:01,767
I...

169
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,300
I'm planning to propose to Seung Ri.

170
00:08:05,967 --> 00:08:06,967
I see.

171
00:08:07,567 --> 00:08:08,767
But why are you telling me that?

172
00:08:09,267 --> 00:08:11,367
What are you going to do
about Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

173
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,500
What does your proposal...

174
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:15,867
have to do with me and Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

175
00:08:15,967 --> 00:08:17,167
Quite a lot, actually.

176
00:08:18,167 --> 00:08:20,867
You're the obstacle standing
in the way of my proposal.

177
00:08:22,067 --> 00:08:23,067
From what I've seen,

178
00:08:23,467 --> 00:08:26,067
neither of you can hide your feelings.

179
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:27,800
You should confess too.

180
00:08:28,867 --> 00:08:30,900
Make things official with her.

181
00:08:31,367 --> 00:08:32,867
I'll handle my own affairs.

182
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,967
If you'll keep talking about this,
I'm leaving.

183
00:08:34,967 --> 00:08:35,967
Seung Ri...

184
00:08:37,567 --> 00:08:39,700
She still hasn't given up hope on you.

185
00:08:40,167 --> 00:08:41,167
So please...

186
00:08:41,867 --> 00:08:43,800
Please make her give up on you.

187
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:45,300
Honestly,

188
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:49,300
I feel like marrying you off
to Ms. Cho Eun Ae myself.

189
00:08:52,767 --> 00:08:55,067
If you're done, I'll be going.

190
00:08:55,667 --> 00:08:56,700
I have a meeting soon.

191
00:08:56,967 --> 00:08:57,967
You know...

192
00:08:59,467 --> 00:09:00,667
I really hate you.

193
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:03,767
I truly hate you.

194
00:09:07,467 --> 00:09:08,767
From childhood until now,

195
00:09:09,667 --> 00:09:11,400
I've never beaten you once.

196
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,400
Not in school, not at work.

197
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:15,067
And even Seung Ri,
the one I want so badly.

198
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:18,900
Why is it always you?

199
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,000
Hey.

200
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:37,167
Oh Hye Ji, did you give up
on the medical licensing exam?

201
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,767
What kind of med student
has this much free time?

202
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,267
Eun Nim, did something happen yesterday?

203
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:47,267
I woke up at dawn and ran off immediately,

204
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:48,767
but I don't remember a thing.

205
00:09:49,267 --> 00:09:51,967
Did I do anything embarrassing
in front of Mr. Seo?

206
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:54,867
You really don't remember at all?

207
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,300
Don't ever drink again.

208
00:09:58,467 --> 00:10:00,600
Why? Was I that bad?

209
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,767
You kept saying the same thing
over and over again.

210
00:10:02,967 --> 00:10:04,500
I thought my ears were going to bleed.

211
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:05,500
What?

212
00:10:05,667 --> 00:10:07,367
What did I keep repeating?

213
00:10:13,567 --> 00:10:14,567
Mr. Seo.

214
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,900
Do you want today to be our first day?

215
00:10:17,267 --> 00:10:19,567
What? Our first day?

216
00:10:19,567 --> 00:10:21,367
Yes! Let's date.

217
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:23,400
What? Let's date?

218
00:10:26,967 --> 00:10:28,367
Okay, deal!

219
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:47,167
Mr. Seo, do you want today
to be our first day?

220
00:10:47,467 --> 00:10:48,467
What?

221
00:10:50,867 --> 00:10:52,067
Okay, deal!

222
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,567
"Do you want today to be our first day?"

223
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:56,267
"Let's date."

224
00:10:57,100 --> 00:10:59,400
You said that about 99 times.

225
00:10:59,667 --> 00:11:00,700
What?

226
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:03,500
So what did Mr. Seo say?

227
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:04,667
I don't know!

228
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:07,467
You two swore all night
that you'd start dating,

229
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:08,967
so good luck with that.

230
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:10,900
Assuming he remembers it too.

231
00:11:11,667 --> 00:11:12,667
What should I do?

232
00:11:12,667 --> 00:11:14,067
Should I call him right now and ask?

233
00:11:14,067 --> 00:11:15,200
If he really wants to date me?

234
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:18,067
But Hye Ji,
what do you even like about him?

235
00:11:18,267 --> 00:11:19,500
I'm genuinely curious.

236
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:22,800
Come on, he's practically Prince Charming.

237
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:26,367
Those long legs, that sharp nose,

238
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,367
those soulful...

239
00:11:31,567 --> 00:11:32,567
Hey.

240
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:35,700
I think there's something wrong
with your eyesight.

241
00:11:36,267 --> 00:11:37,767
You need an eye exam urgently.

242
00:11:38,167 --> 00:11:40,200
How is that slick-talking guy a prince?

243
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:43,567
What happened?

244
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:46,367
I remember having drinks with Hye Ji.

245
00:11:48,967 --> 00:11:50,767
(Oh Hye Ji)

246
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:54,067
What do I do?

247
00:11:54,067 --> 00:11:56,667
Did I do anything bad? Seriously.

248
00:11:57,567 --> 00:11:58,800
Answer it? Or not?

249
00:11:58,900 --> 00:11:59,867
- Answer it?
- Oh Hye Ji?

250
00:11:59,867 --> 00:12:01,567
- You scared me!
- Why aren't you answering?

251
00:12:02,067 --> 00:12:03,067
You scared me!

252
00:12:03,567 --> 00:12:05,667
Make some noise when you come in!

253
00:12:06,167 --> 00:12:07,167
Who is Oh Hye Ji?

254
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,567
- The writer?
- No, nothing like that.

255
00:12:11,367 --> 00:12:13,700
Do you think she's the only person
who ever calls me?

256
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:15,100
Then who is it?

257
00:12:16,067 --> 00:12:17,967
Wait, do you have a girlfriend now?

258
00:12:18,167 --> 00:12:19,167
What?

259
00:12:19,367 --> 00:12:21,067
No way.

260
00:12:21,067 --> 00:12:22,067
Right?

261
00:12:22,967 --> 00:12:23,967
What do you mean, right?

262
00:12:24,267 --> 00:12:25,867
Am I not allowed to have a girlfriend?

263
00:12:26,967 --> 00:12:29,367
I'm only the punching bag at home.

264
00:12:29,367 --> 00:12:31,067
Outside, I'm quite popular.

265
00:12:32,267 --> 00:12:34,500
Why did you come in?
I thought you weren't feeling well.

266
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:38,100
I was going to ask if you wanted me...

267
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:41,067
to pack you something for dinner
to share with the writer.

268
00:12:41,467 --> 00:12:42,667
No.

269
00:12:42,867 --> 00:12:45,967
My relationship with that writer
is way beyond what snacks can fix.

270
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:48,200
So don't bother.

271
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:50,767
Just how bad is your relationship?

272
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,167
Get out. I'm busy.

273
00:12:53,167 --> 00:12:54,267
Get out. Okay? Get out.

274
00:12:54,267 --> 00:12:55,667
Eat a good dinner before you go...

275
00:12:55,667 --> 00:12:57,367
if you're pulling another all-nighter.

276
00:12:58,167 --> 00:12:59,367
What's this now?

277
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,667
Yes, Your Majesty.

278
00:13:06,867 --> 00:13:08,100
("The ER Witch" Writer)

279
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:10,167
Should I just ask her directly?

280
00:13:10,867 --> 00:13:11,667
("The ER Witch" Writer)

281
00:13:13,767 --> 00:13:14,767
Whatever.

282
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:18,567
Even if I did make a fool of myself,
she'll probably forget soon enough.

283
00:13:18,667 --> 00:13:20,367
She's a goldfish, after all.

284
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:29,567
(Goldfish)

285
00:13:34,167 --> 00:13:35,267
I'm home.

286
00:13:35,667 --> 00:13:37,300
Hey, you're home early.

287
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:40,900
Why are you wearing sunglasses indoors?

288
00:13:41,167 --> 00:13:43,200
Right. My eyes are a little...

289
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:46,500
Why? Do you have pink eye or something?

290
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:48,900
No, it's nothing.

291
00:13:49,067 --> 00:13:50,667
If you're not feeling well,
go get some rest.

292
00:13:50,667 --> 00:13:51,667
Yes, Mother.

293
00:13:54,567 --> 00:13:57,767
Looks like she really did something
to upset you, Madam.

294
00:13:58,067 --> 00:13:59,067
What?

295
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:02,267
It's just that she seems desperate...

296
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:03,900
to avoid making eye contact with you.

297
00:14:03,967 --> 00:14:06,967
Did my chess partner go somewhere?

298
00:14:07,267 --> 00:14:08,467
Checkmate.

299
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:11,000
It's a dead end again.

300
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:12,867
I lost this round too.

301
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,567
Are you losing on purpose?

302
00:14:17,667 --> 00:14:19,267
What if I end up having a heart attack?

303
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:20,967
My nerves can't take this.

304
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:28,967
Honey, did you find out?

305
00:14:30,167 --> 00:14:31,267
What do you mean, what?

306
00:14:32,567 --> 00:14:34,200
Mr. Cho's wife's birthday.

307
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:36,667
You have to find out, okay?

308
00:14:39,667 --> 00:14:41,700
What a ticking time bomb.

309
00:14:42,067 --> 00:14:43,167
What am I going to do?

310
00:14:43,267 --> 00:14:45,467
Sorry? My wife's birthday?

311
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:47,100
Why do you ask?

312
00:14:47,300 --> 00:14:50,067
Come on.

313
00:14:50,067 --> 00:14:53,167
All Kangsu Construction employees
are practically family to me.

314
00:14:53,967 --> 00:14:56,667
I just want to celebrate
my family's family's birthdays too.

315
00:14:57,567 --> 00:14:59,667
No, that's really not necessary...

316
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:01,967
Come on, just tell me.

317
00:15:02,467 --> 00:15:04,867
What's so hard about giving me
four digits?

318
00:15:06,767 --> 00:15:07,800
Four digits?

319
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:11,000
Well, birthdays are usually...

320
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,467
four numbers, right?

321
00:15:12,867 --> 00:15:16,267
Like August 15 would be 0815.

322
00:15:16,867 --> 00:15:17,867
So hurry up.

323
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:21,067
It's February 4th.

324
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:24,367
Really? February 4th.

325
00:15:24,767 --> 00:15:27,567
That'd be 0204.

326
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:31,400
Her birthday already passed this year.

327
00:15:32,467 --> 00:15:36,067
And stop driving me
to and from work from now on.

328
00:15:36,967 --> 00:15:39,900
Why? Did you hire a driver?

329
00:15:40,867 --> 00:15:42,967
No, not yet.
But I'm going to start looking.

330
00:15:43,867 --> 00:15:46,267
You've worked hard all this time, Mr. Cho.

331
00:15:47,067 --> 00:15:50,467
Then at least until you hire one...

332
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:51,567
I said it's fine!

333
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:53,500
Just go home.

334
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:56,200
Yes, sir. I'll leave after you do.

335
00:15:56,367 --> 00:15:57,600
There you go again!

336
00:15:57,967 --> 00:16:01,500
Why can't you ever just do
what the CEO says the first time?

337
00:16:02,867 --> 00:16:05,467
Understood. Then I'll head home first.

338
00:16:08,167 --> 00:16:09,167
Bye.

339
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:11,867
And don't ever come near my house again.

340
00:16:12,967 --> 00:16:15,100
Seriously.
I really shot myself in the foot.

341
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:17,000
Why did I hire him as my assistant?

342
00:16:18,267 --> 00:16:19,767
So, 0204...

343
00:16:23,867 --> 00:16:26,367
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, I reviewed the Joy report.

344
00:16:26,700 --> 00:16:28,500
Okay, thank you.

345
00:16:29,167 --> 00:16:31,467
I sent it out in a company-wide email,
so take a look, everyone.

346
00:16:31,767 --> 00:16:32,767
- Okay.
- Okay.

347
00:16:33,567 --> 00:16:36,267
I have something to do,
so I'll be leaving first.

348
00:16:36,667 --> 00:16:37,700
All right.

349
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:40,567
See you tomorrow, Manager Seo.

350
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:41,900
Goodbye.

351
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:09,767
Dad.

352
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,800
Your daughter is the worst.

353
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:15,767
I never realized until today...

354
00:17:16,467 --> 00:17:17,667
just how pathetic and inadequate I am.

355
00:17:20,367 --> 00:17:23,767
Everyone has pathetic
and inadequate sides to them.

356
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:28,067
The fact that you've realized yours today
is enough.

357
00:17:29,267 --> 00:17:30,267
Lift your head.

358
00:17:30,767 --> 00:17:33,067
This isn't the end of your story.

359
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:38,000
What if I keep being pathetic?
What if I only get worse?

360
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:41,667
I'm scared I'll fall apart.

361
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:43,767
I'm scared I'll become even more broken.

362
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:48,667
You were about six years old, I think.

363
00:17:50,367 --> 00:17:53,367
Back when I was struggling
after my business failed,

364
00:17:54,667 --> 00:17:55,900
you said this to me.

365
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,200
"Dad."

366
00:17:58,867 --> 00:18:02,167
"If you fall down,
you can just get back up."

367
00:18:03,267 --> 00:18:05,800
"So make sure you get back up."

368
00:18:07,267 --> 00:18:10,167
Back then,
I didn't even know what was happening.

369
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:14,167
I just knew you looked sad.

370
00:18:15,167 --> 00:18:17,200
And it was something you always told me.

371
00:18:17,667 --> 00:18:18,667
I know.

372
00:18:19,467 --> 00:18:22,467
But those words
gave me tremendous strength.

373
00:18:25,867 --> 00:18:26,867
Dad.

374
00:18:27,900 --> 00:18:31,200
You haven't challenged me
to many practice matches,

375
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,800
but every time you did,
you never backed down.

376
00:18:36,867 --> 00:18:37,867
Right now,

377
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:41,867
you're just lost because you don't know
where to point your bamboo sword.

378
00:18:43,167 --> 00:18:44,400
Think carefully.

379
00:18:45,467 --> 00:18:47,667
If you're standing here...

380
00:18:48,767 --> 00:18:50,400
holding a bamboo sword for the first time,

381
00:18:53,167 --> 00:18:56,067
you need to figure out
exactly where you want to strike.

382
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:59,367
Then charge straight through.

383
00:19:00,667 --> 00:19:02,067
I know you can do it.

384
00:19:03,467 --> 00:19:05,167
Charge straight through?

385
00:19:10,767 --> 00:19:11,767
I'm home.

386
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:14,400
I was just about to set the table.

387
00:19:14,667 --> 00:19:15,767
Perfect timing.

388
00:19:15,967 --> 00:19:17,867
I guess I'm lucky when it comes to food.

389
00:19:18,367 --> 00:19:19,500
Hello.

390
00:19:20,567 --> 00:19:22,100
Why are you alone? Where's Eun Ae?

391
00:19:22,467 --> 00:19:24,767
She said she had somewhere to stop by.
We left the office separately.

392
00:19:24,967 --> 00:19:25,967
Hi, Bit Na.

393
00:19:26,367 --> 00:19:27,500
I'm home.

394
00:19:28,067 --> 00:19:29,867
He said you were stopping somewhere,
but you're back already.

395
00:19:30,067 --> 00:19:31,567
Perfect. I'll set the table now.

396
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:33,967
Go change first and come downstairs.
You too, Team Manager Ko.

397
00:19:34,767 --> 00:19:36,167
Bit Na, let's eat.

398
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:37,500
Okay, I'll be right down.

399
00:19:42,167 --> 00:19:44,167
What's wrong?
Did you and Team Manager Ko fight?

400
00:19:44,567 --> 00:19:45,667
Fight? No way.

401
00:19:45,967 --> 00:19:47,800
Just go help Mom.

402
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:50,200
What's going on?

403
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:58,967
Since I was buying one anyway,
I bought one more.

404
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:00,600
I wonder if Mom will like it.

405
00:20:10,067 --> 00:20:11,267
What's this?

406
00:20:19,467 --> 00:20:21,500
I broke this by accident
when I was five...

407
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:22,900
and got scolded so badly for it.

408
00:20:24,167 --> 00:20:25,900
She still kept it?

409
00:20:26,167 --> 00:20:27,167
My goodness.

410
00:20:29,100 --> 00:20:32,367
This looks really old too. What is this?

411
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:36,267
Eun Ae, Team Manager Ko.

412
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:37,800
Hurry and come out.

413
00:20:38,267 --> 00:20:39,600
Yes, I'm coming.

414
00:20:47,267 --> 00:20:48,467
Team Manager, wait a second.

415
00:20:49,067 --> 00:20:50,767
Where did you stop by?

416
00:20:50,767 --> 00:20:52,767
If you were coming right back,
we could've gone together.

417
00:20:53,900 --> 00:20:54,900
Here.

418
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:56,800
What's this?

419
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:58,767
A housewarming gift.

420
00:20:59,067 --> 00:21:00,600
What? A housewarming gift?

421
00:21:01,367 --> 00:21:04,367
Wait, did you leave by yourself
just to buy this?

422
00:21:06,567 --> 00:21:07,567
Towels?

423
00:21:07,567 --> 00:21:09,800
But there are plenty of towels
in the bathroom already.

424
00:21:10,667 --> 00:21:13,400
I've been meaning to get these for you.
I just never had the time.

425
00:21:14,467 --> 00:21:16,467
Seriously. What kind of rich heir...

426
00:21:16,467 --> 00:21:18,567
moves in without bringing a single towel?

427
00:21:18,700 --> 00:21:21,200
What heir uses others' towels?

428
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:22,800
You're being harsh.

429
00:21:23,167 --> 00:21:25,400
Are you really scolding me
over a few towels?

430
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:28,267
But these are totally my style.

431
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:32,767
They're thicker than the ones here.

432
00:21:32,967 --> 00:21:36,667
And I picked the colors
with your preferences in mind.

433
00:21:37,667 --> 00:21:39,167
It may not seem like much,

434
00:21:39,167 --> 00:21:41,500
but little things like this
can really lift your mood.

435
00:21:42,067 --> 00:21:43,067
Thank you.

436
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:46,067
I'll make sure these towels
help me unwind.

437
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:50,467
Since you got me a housewarming gift,
how about a housewarming party...

438
00:21:51,167 --> 00:21:52,867
- What?
- Never mind.

439
00:21:53,667 --> 00:21:54,867
Mom says to come downstairs.

440
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,467
Okay.
I'll wash my hands and come right down.

441
00:22:06,367 --> 00:22:07,367
- Honey.
- Yeah?

442
00:22:08,767 --> 00:22:12,300
Your boss's wife came by today.

443
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:15,067
Who? CEO Ko's wife?

444
00:22:16,867 --> 00:22:18,967
Did she find out Team Manager Ko
is staying here?

445
00:22:19,900 --> 00:22:21,967
That's what I thought at first.

446
00:22:22,767 --> 00:22:24,167
But she didn't say a word about it.

447
00:22:24,167 --> 00:22:26,100
The moment she saw me, she just left.

448
00:22:26,467 --> 00:22:27,567
Without saying anything?

449
00:22:27,567 --> 00:22:30,167
Yeah. She left like she was being chased.

450
00:22:30,167 --> 00:22:32,367
I didn't even get a chance to talk to her.

451
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:35,167
I don't like her.

452
00:22:37,567 --> 00:22:39,967
Did CEO Ko say anything to you?

453
00:22:39,967 --> 00:22:41,900
Not really.

454
00:22:43,167 --> 00:22:45,667
He did ask when your birthday is.

455
00:22:46,067 --> 00:22:48,800
He said employees' families
are like his own family,

456
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:49,867
so he wanted to celebrate it.

457
00:22:50,067 --> 00:22:51,067
Please.

458
00:22:51,667 --> 00:22:53,467
As if we're really family to him.

459
00:22:54,667 --> 00:22:57,567
Those two are exactly alike.

460
00:22:58,067 --> 00:23:00,267
There's no end to resentment.

461
00:23:00,267 --> 00:23:01,267
Just let it go.

462
00:23:03,167 --> 00:23:04,467
How was Bit Na today?

463
00:23:06,100 --> 00:23:07,167
Well...

464
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:11,167
Kids can tell when something's wrong too.

465
00:23:13,067 --> 00:23:16,800
I really need to meet Ji Seon.

466
00:23:17,767 --> 00:23:20,467
I told you not to get involved.

467
00:23:23,067 --> 00:23:24,067
Is that Eun Hyeong?

468
00:23:24,667 --> 00:23:27,167
It's me. I'm going for a run
around the neighborhood.

469
00:23:27,867 --> 00:23:28,967
Okay.

470
00:23:31,867 --> 00:23:33,200
Didn't Eun Ae and Team Manager Ko...

471
00:23:33,667 --> 00:23:36,267
seem a little awkward today?

472
00:23:37,767 --> 00:23:38,767
I don't know.

473
00:23:41,967 --> 00:23:42,967
Mom.

474
00:23:42,967 --> 00:23:44,900
There.

475
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:45,900
There.

476
00:24:02,367 --> 00:24:05,967
Do you really have to go?

477
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:23,800
Cho Eun Ae.

478
00:24:24,467 --> 00:24:26,567
He said no.

479
00:24:27,867 --> 00:24:29,467
Please stop thinking about it.

480
00:24:30,767 --> 00:24:31,767
Good work.

481
00:24:37,700 --> 00:24:39,067
Wasn't it urgent?

482
00:24:39,567 --> 00:24:42,567
You stopped our entire team's work
and had her spend two full days on it.

483
00:24:42,667 --> 00:24:43,800
The least you could do is review it.

484
00:24:45,667 --> 00:24:48,567
He was only protecting his team member.
Nothing more, nothing less.

485
00:24:49,667 --> 00:24:50,867
Get a grip, Cho Eun Ae.

486
00:25:04,467 --> 00:25:05,567
Did you just finish your workout?

487
00:25:06,667 --> 00:25:07,667
Yes.

488
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:09,400
A healthy body makes a strong nation,
after all.

489
00:25:10,467 --> 00:25:12,500
But why are you out here?

490
00:25:13,767 --> 00:25:15,467
Just thinking about a few things.

491
00:25:15,967 --> 00:25:17,767
- Let's go inside.
- Team Manager.

492
00:25:18,767 --> 00:25:20,200
There's something I want to say.

493
00:25:21,567 --> 00:25:23,800
Why were you like that
with Manager Seo today?

494
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:27,400
You're already swamped as a team member.

495
00:25:28,267 --> 00:25:30,267
After pulling you away from your work
and assigning you something else,

496
00:25:30,667 --> 00:25:32,067
the least she could do
was review it right away.

497
00:25:32,867 --> 00:25:36,800
Did you really have to go that far?

498
00:25:38,067 --> 00:25:39,667
Why are you so cold?

499
00:25:40,767 --> 00:25:42,800
I'm cold?

500
00:25:43,267 --> 00:25:44,367
Aren't you?

501
00:25:47,700 --> 00:25:50,267
I think you grew up
surrounded by a lot of love.

502
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:53,200
What? Where is this coming from?

503
00:25:53,767 --> 00:25:56,067
People who deeply empathize
with others' pain...

504
00:25:56,667 --> 00:25:58,367
have a lot of love inside them.

505
00:25:59,567 --> 00:26:01,300
It became clear after seeing your family.

506
00:26:02,367 --> 00:26:03,867
No matter how much they argue,

507
00:26:04,867 --> 00:26:06,267
they truly care about each other.

508
00:26:07,567 --> 00:26:10,567
All that love must've built up inside you.

509
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:14,067
You ignore other people's pain...

510
00:26:14,367 --> 00:26:16,600
and always say exactly what's right.

511
00:26:17,100 --> 00:26:18,200
Does that mean you have affection issues?

512
00:26:19,167 --> 00:26:22,000
Yes. I do. I have affection issues.

513
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:26,467
I didn't grow up warm and loved
the way you did.

514
00:26:27,367 --> 00:26:29,100
Come on...

515
00:26:30,267 --> 00:26:31,800
Why are you taking a joke so seriously?

516
00:26:33,900 --> 00:26:36,067
I'm sorry. I shouldn't have said that.

517
00:26:37,367 --> 00:26:38,467
See?

518
00:26:39,867 --> 00:26:42,200
You apologized right away
because you're worried you hurt me.

519
00:26:43,067 --> 00:26:44,767
I'm telling you,
you're overflowing with love.

520
00:26:49,967 --> 00:26:51,200
You don't need to apologize.

521
00:26:52,067 --> 00:26:53,200
I'm okay.

522
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:55,000
Let's go inside.

523
00:26:55,967 --> 00:26:56,967
Team Manager.

524
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:01,767
I...

525
00:27:04,567 --> 00:27:05,567
like you.

526
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:13,067
I...

527
00:27:16,100 --> 00:27:17,167
like you...

528
00:27:18,967 --> 00:27:19,967
very much.

529
00:27:22,967 --> 00:27:23,967
A whole lot.

530
00:28:11,500 --> 00:28:14,167
(Our Happy Days)

531
00:28:14,367 --> 00:28:16,667
Now it really begins, okay?

532
00:28:16,667 --> 00:28:17,667
What's gotten into Seo Seung Ri?

533
00:28:17,667 --> 00:28:20,867
She seems different. Full of energy.

534
00:28:22,867 --> 00:28:25,000
Is there anyone you like?

535
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:28,300
I don't want that person to get hurt
because of me.

536
00:28:28,300 --> 00:28:32,367
That precious feeling
may come only once in your life,

537
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:35,300
I hope you never let it slip away.

538
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:37,167
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
